$interpreted: Leah: ... Didn't I tell you in the letter that there's no need to visit me!?

Lio: B, but sis, Nigel and the others are all worried about you... I missed you a lot as well... 
Sis, can't you come back every once in a while...

Leah: The Academy's workload is tough. I don't have the time to go back...
You shouldn't come here again in the future.
Lio: Wha... Sis, that's so mean!
Leah: What's that about? When and where was I mean!?
Fredrica: Excuse me~ If you want to bicker, would you mind taking it somewhere else other than the middle of the road?
Leah: All in all, I don't need you guys to worry about me!
Leah: Also, you should stop bringing things to me. Whistlewood Valley is not exactly a saf...

Lio: Sister, you don't care about us at all!
If you want to stay here so much, then don't come back, forever!
Leah: Oh, is that where we are going? Fine then! I won't go back ever again!
Lio: Sister... Sis you big dumb idiot! I won't care about you anymore!
Leah: Lio...
Charle: I was expecting you, Miss Lucien. Are you here to brew your potion again this year?
Fredrica: I would prefer not returning every year too. But the... "Water of Eternal Youth" can only be brewed legally at Rune Academy. So~ here I am again.

Leah: Water of Eternal Youth?
That sounds like some hocus-pocus nonsense!
Fredrica: Hey, you. Stay where you are.
Leah: Hmm? What?
Fredrica: Headmaster, this... little bunny, can you lend her to me for a few days?
Charle: What do you need Miss Leah for?
Fredrica: Well, as headmaster may know, the Water of Eternal Youth requires some~ tricky ingredients. I want my cute junior to give me a helping hand~
Charle: Hmmm...
Leah: I! DON'T! WANT TO! Headmaster, I don't want anything to do with this old hag!
Charle: I guess it's fine.
Leah: Headmaster!?
Charle: Miss Lucien is one of the best sorcerers the Academy has produced. I'm sure Miss Leah can learn a lot by accompanying her on this journey.
Fredrica: Fantastic! Since we have the headmaster's permission already, let's get moving~
Leah: Let go of me! You old hag! Stupid witch!!
Leah: This forest is huge. How would I know where to find that damn fruit...
Leah: Weird face... Could this be the fruit the old hag is looking for?
Fredrica: Not too shabby, little bunny. You found quite a lot of them...
Fredrica: Eww, why is it sticky?
Leah: Just what in the world is this fruit?
Fredrica: It's called the Pomelodora. During this time of year, they are at their sweetest and most fragrant~
Fredrica: On top of that, its skin is a key ingredient for the "Water of Eternal Youth".
Leah: (... A sweet and fragrant fruit, Lio's probably going to like it, right? I'll mail one back to him. That way, he won't be mad at me anymore!)
